{{Use Australian English|date=November 2016}} {{ Infobox V8 Supercar race report | flag = Northern Territory | title = 2017 CrownBet Darwin Triple Crown | round_no = 6 | season_no = 14 | year = 2017 | series = IVSC | track_map = Hidden Valley Raceway (Australia) track map.svg | date = 16–18 June | location = [[Darwin, Northern Territory|Darwin]], [[Northern Territory]] | circuit = Hidden Valley Raceway | weather = | race1_laps = 42 | race1_dist = 120 | pole1 = {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Rick Kelly]] | pole1_team = [[Nissan Motorsport (Australia)|Nissan Motorsport]] | pole1_time = 1:05.7114 | winner1 = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Fabian Coulthard]] | winner1_team = [[DJR Team Penske]] | winner1_time = 52:28.2817 | race2_laps = 70 | race2_dist = 200 | pole2 = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Scott McLaughlin (racing driver)|Scott McLaughlin]] | pole2_team = [[DJR Team Penske]] | pole2_time = 1:05.7232 | winner2 = {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Scott McLaughlin (racing driver)|Scott McLaughlin]] | winner2_team = [[DJR Team Penske]] | winner2_time = 1:21:04.2732 }}
The '''2017 CrownBet Darwin Triple Crown''' was an [[auto racing|motor racing]] event for the [[Supercars Championship]], held on the weekend of 16 to 18 June 2017. The event was held at [[Hidden Valley Raceway]] near [[Darwin, Northern Territory|Darwin]] in the [[Northern Territory]] and consisted of two races, 120 and 200 kilometres in length. It is the sixth event of fourteen in the [[2017 Supercars Championship]] and hosted Races 11 and 12 of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.supercars.com/2017-crownbet-darwin-triple-crown-schedule-results/|title=2017 CrownBet Darwin Triple Crown Schedule & Results |website=Supercars.com|accessdate=11 December 2017}}</ref>
==Background== ===Driver changes=== [[Taz Douglas]] was replaced at [[Lucas Dumbrell Motorsport]] with [[Cameron McConville]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.speedcafe.com/2017/06/10/mcconville-make-supercars-return-ldm/|title=McConville to make Supercars return with LDM - Speedcafe|website=Speedcafe.com|accessdate=11 December 2017}}</ref>
This was the third round in which [[2017 Dunlop Super2 Series|Super2 Series]] wildcards were allowed to compete in the main class. [[Jack Le Brocq]] and [[Macauley Jones]] were the two drivers to step up for this round.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.speedcafe.com/2017/04/20/wildcards-locked-winton-darwin-ipswich/|title=Wildcards locked in for Winton, Darwin, Ipswich - Speedcafe|website=Speedcafe.com|accessdate=11 December 2017}}</ref>
