'''Kosmos Global Holding S.L.''', also known as '''Kosmos Holding''' or '''Kosmos''', is a global sports and media investment group headquartered in Barcelona, Spain.

Founded in 2017 by [[FC Barcelona]] and [[Spanish national football team]] player [[Gerard Piqué]], the company is backed by [[Hiroshi Mikitani]], chairman and CEO of [[Rakuten]]. The other founders of Kosmos are Edmund Chu, Nullah Sarker, and Michael Evans.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.economiadigital.es/directivos-y-empresas/gerard-pique-monta-su-ultimo-negocio-con-sus-colegas-de-harvard_543422_102.html|title=Gerard Piqué monta su último negocio con dos 'colegas' de Harvard|website=Economiadigital (ed. general)|access-date=2018-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704130939/https://www.economiadigital.es/directivos-y-empresas/gerard-pique-monta-su-ultimo-negocio-con-sus-colegas-de-harvard_543422_102.html|archive-date=2018-07-04|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://worldfootballsummit.com/world-football-summit-transform-madrid-world-capital-football-industry/|title=WFS, ready to transform Madrid in the world capital of the football industry - World Football Summit|website=Worldfootballsummit.com|access-date=2018-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113171751/https://worldfootballsummit.com/world-football-summit-transform-madrid-world-capital-football-industry/|archive-date=2018-11-13|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://atlas.world/member/edmund-chu/|title=Edmund Chu - Atlas Network|website=Atlas.world|access-date=2018-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113170204/https://atlas.world/member/edmund-chu/|archive-date=2018-11-13|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.palco23.com/competiciones/pique-ficha-talento-de-wwp-y-asics-para-preparar-su-entrada-en-el-negocio-del-tenis.html|title=Piqué ficha talento de WWP y Asics para preparar su entrada en el negocio del tenis|website=Palco23.com|access-date=2018-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113170237/https://www.palco23.com/competiciones/pique-ficha-talento-de-wwp-y-asics-para-preparar-su-entrada-en-el-negocio-del-tenis.html|archive-date=2018-11-13|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref>{{Excessive citations inline |date=November 2018}}

== Activities ==
On February 26, 2018, Kosmos announced plans to invest $3 billion over 25 years in the [[Davis Cup]] by [[BNP Paribas]]. Kosmos will partner with the [[International Tennis Federation]] to transform the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/sports/report/major-davis-cup-shake-up-approved/20180816.htm|title=Major Davis Cup shake-up approved - Rediff.com Sports|website=Rediff.com|access-date=2018-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113210351/http://www.rediff.com/sports/report/major-davis-cup-shake-up-approved/20180816.htm|archive-date=2018-11-13|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> On August 6, 2018, [[Larry Ellison]] published a letter announcing that he will be joining Kosmos as an investor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-tennis-daviscup/ellison-excited-for-indian-wells-to-host-revamped-davis-cup-idUSKBN1KS12V|title=Ellison excited for Indian Wells to host revamped Davis Cup|first=Reuters|last=Editorial|website=Reuters.com|access-date=2018-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180808215746/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-tennis-daviscup/ellison-excited-for-indian-wells-to-host-revamped-davis-cup-idUSKBN1KS12V|archive-date=2018-08-08|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eu.desertsun.com/story/sports/tennis/2018/08/06/larry-ellisons-help-could-davis-cup-make-its-way-indian-wells-tennis-world-cup-federer-nadal-serena/919947002/|title=With Larry Ellison's help, could Davis Cup make its way to Indian Wells?|website=Eu.desertsun.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tennispanorama.com/archives/63137|title=BNP Paribas Open Tournament Owner Larry Ellison Supports New Davis Cup Format - Tennis Panorama|date=6 August 2018|website=Tennispanorama.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.infocif.es/cargos-administrador/kosmos-global-holding-sl|title=Cargos y administradores de KOSMOS GLOBAL HOLDING SL B67112656|website=Infocif.es}}</ref>{{Excessive citations inline |date=November 2018}}

== Criticism of Davis Cup ==
Kosmos partnership with the International Tennis Federation to revamp the Davis Cup has been criticized by the tennis community. Many claim that the partnership will take away from the traditions of the 118-year-old tennis event.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/tennis/story/_/id/22595981/davis-cup-revamp-plans-hold-event-one-location-seven-days-november-get-mixed-response|title=Davis Cup revamp plans get mixed response|website=Espn.com|access-date=2018-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180523172112/http://www.espn.com/tennis/story/_/id/22595981/davis-cup-revamp-plans-hold-event-one-location-seven-days-november-get-mixed-response|archive-date=2018-05-23|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> In a secret meeting held in Orlando, Florida, on August 16, 2018, the changes proposed by Kosmos received a 71 percent approval at the International Tennis Federation annual general meeting. Proposals require a two-thirds majority to pass.<ref name="nytimes.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/08/16/sports/davis-cup-vote-itf.html|title=Davis Cup Overhaul Wins Approval From Tennis Officials|website=Nytimes.com|access-date=2018-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180817181723/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/08/16/sports/davis-cup-vote-itf.html|archive-date=2018-08-17|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> While France and USA voice strong support for the changes and voted in favor of the move, others, such as Australia, were against the new format.<ref name="nytimes.com"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sport24.co.za/Tennis/itf-delegates-approve-radical-davis-cup-overhaul-20180816|title=ITF delegates approve radical Davis Cup overhaul|website=Sport24.co.za|access-date=2018-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180817113120/https://www.sport24.co.za/Tennis/itf-delegates-approve-radical-davis-cup-overhaul-20180816|archive-date=2018-08-17|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/tennis/43202373|title=Davis Cup: ITF plans to introduce 18-team World Cup of Tennis Finals in revamp|date=26 February 2018|website=Bbc.com|access-date=2018-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113225108/https://www.bbc.com/sport/tennis/43202373|archive-date=2018-11-13|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref>{{Excessive citations inline |date=November 2018}}

After the vote, French player Nicolas Mahut tweeted, "The Davis Cup died, and a part of the history of our sport flew away for a handful of dollars". <ref name="nytimes.com"/> Other players on the circuit including [[Novak Djokovic]], [[Andy Murray]], and [[Rafael Nadal]] have publicly supported the new idea.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurosport.com/tennis/gerard-pique-s-tennis-world-cup-plan-backed-by-andy-murray-novak-djokovic-and-rafael-nadal_sto6162644/story.shtml|title=Gerard Pique's 'Tennis World Cup' plan backed by English player Andy Murray, Serbian Novak Djokovic and fellow Spaniard Rafael Nadal|date=12 May 2017|website=Eurosport.com|access-date=2018-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113170045/https://www.eurosport.com/tennis/gerard-pique-s-tennis-world-cup-plan-backed-by-andy-murray-novak-djokovic-and-rafael-nadal_sto6162644/story.shtml|archive-date=2018-11-13|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> Lleyton Hewitt of Australia strongly opposes the new initiative as an erosion of the 100-year-old tradition of the Davis Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tennis.com/pro-game/2018/08/weighing-pros-and-cons-itfs-roll-dice-davis-cup-revamp/76079/|title=Weighing the pros and cons of the ITF's roll-the-dice Davis Cup revamp|website=Tennis.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euronews.com/2018/08/04/tennis-itf-defend-3-billion-davis-cup-revamp-despite-criticism|title=Tennis - ITF defend $3 billion Davis Cup revamp despite criticism|date=4 August 2018|website=Euronews.com|access-date=2018-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113210814/https://www.euronews.com/2018/08/04/tennis-itf-defend-3-billion-davis-cup-revamp-despite-criticism|archive-date=2018-11-13|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref>{{Failed verification|date=November 2018}}

